On Thu, 20 Jan 2005 12:16:35 -0800, Gordon Mohr (Internet Archive)
&lt;gojomo@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; Sam wrote:
&gt; &gt; We just updated to the most recent version of Heritrix from CVS on our
&gt; &gt; project, and we were confused to find that our list of seed URIs now
&gt; &gt; seems to be interpreted as a list of files from which to get seeds.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The description for seeds (on new.jsp) still says:
&gt; &gt; &quot;Fill in seed URIs below, one per line. Comment lines begin with &#39;#&#39;.&quot;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; When I view the settings after setting some seeds, however, it says,
&gt; &gt; &quot;Seed list too large to edit&quot; under seeds, with the words &quot;seed list&quot;
&gt; &gt; linking to what I put in the seeds box.  This happens even if we only
&gt; &gt; list one seed.  What is going on?
&gt; 
&gt; This is probably the result of a recent bug fix in HEAD.
&gt; 
&gt;   [ 1102755 ] seeds text area truncates seeds; big seed lists break config
&gt;   http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1102755&group_id=73833&atid=539099
&gt; 
&gt; The problem that motivated the change is that the browser textarea
&gt; cannot contain very large seed lists -- in fact in some cases a large
&gt; list sent back from the server will cause long pauses or rendering
&gt; problems on the &#39;settings&#39; page, and lead to a textarea with truncated
&gt; contents.
&gt; 
&gt; If the settings page does display, and is then resubmitted, you can
&gt; wind up inadvertently losing seeds you&#39;d previously entered.
&gt; 
&gt; To guard against this, code was added to disable the textarea
&gt; display for seed lists &gt; 32K. That limit is arbitrary; I could
&gt; not find a definitive reference for practical browser implementation
&gt; limits in this regard.
&gt; 
&gt; You shouldn&#39;t see this problem listing a single-seed, unless you&#39;ve got
&gt; a ton of non-URL content (comments?) in your entry.
&gt; 
&gt; If you are seeing it with tiny seed lists, there&#39;s a bug in the fix.
&gt; 
&gt; More generally, the method for entering and changing seeds needs
&gt; reworking to better support large seed lists via the web UI.
&gt; 
&gt; - Gordon
